                <note rend="inline" type="source">Doc. No. 13 (G).</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum on the Clauses of the Draft Treaty Concerning
                        Bilateral Treaties</hi> (Art. 37.)</head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                        calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1946-10-15T23:59:59+01:00"
                        notBefore="1946-08-20T00:00:00+01:00">undated</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Article</hi> 37</p>
                <p>According to Article 37 as worded in the Draft Treaty, each Allied or Associated
                    Power can, within 6 months of the coming into force of the Treaty, notify Italy
                    which pre-war bilateral treaties it desires to keep in force or revive.</p>
            </div>
